The introduction of symnyms, to any considerable extent, into a work so elementary as this, is a feature almost, if not - wholly new; and it is hoped that it may not prove unacceptable to those of my fellow-teachers especially, who are engaged in preparing young men for college. The practice of discrimi- nating between words whose general meanings arc the same, or similar, cannot fail to have a most salutary influence upon men- tal development and accurate scholar-ship.
